    "description": "\nWinter weather travel advisory in effect.\n\nWhat:\nSnow, at times heavy. Total snowfall amounts of 10 to 15 cm.\nPeak snowfall rates of 2 to 4 cm per hour.\nReduced visibility in snow and local blowing snow.\n\nWhen:\nEarly Monday morning through early Tuesday morning.\n\nAdditional information:\nAn upgrade to a snowfall warning may be required. Snow is expected to taper to flurries early Tuesday morning.\n\nIn addition, northerly winds will intensify Monday afternoon with gusts up to 60 km/h resulting in local blowing snow.\n\n###\n\nFor road conditions and other traveller information from the Ministry of Transportation, visit https://www.ontario.ca/511, https://www.twitter.com/511Ontario, or call 5-1-1.\n\nPlease continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@ec.gc.ca or post reports on X using #ONStorm.\n",
    "instruction": "\nBe prepared to adjust your driving with changing road conditions. If visibility is reduced while driving, slow down, watch for tail lights ahead and be prepared to stop.\n",
